english:
  title: Farewell to An Jun Upon His Appointment as County Magistrate of An Gorge
  author: Kim Soo-on
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your father once walked beside me as a friend,
    How often we sat at leisure in the county office,
    Today, beholding you, all those old ties return—
    And age, encountering these scenes, stirs my weary heart.

    Stone fields lie barren, people scattered far,
    No one plants seeds when spring arrives.
    The grass-roofed hall nestles deep in mountains,
    Where even noon grows dim with shadow.

    This land is one of deepest solitude,
    Yet you must nurture your people's livelihood.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: An Jun is being appointed to An Gorge County (安峽縣), a remote and impoverished region.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'stone fields' and 'scattered people' suggest the county's economic hardship and depopulation.
  - key: ''
    value: The speaker, having served in government alongside An Jun's father, now entrusts the younger man with the difficult task of revitalizing this troubled place.
